# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   Comment this out if so.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1053, Checkfile should be committed.
#   But Pipfile.lock contains system-specific details and should be ignored.
#   https://pipenv.pypa.io/en/latest/advanced/#pipfile-vs-pipfile-lock
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains system-specific details and should be ignored in some cases.
#   However, for applications, it's recommended to commit poetry.lock.
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock contains system-specific details and should be ignored in some cases.
#   However, for applications, it's recommended to commit pdm.lock.
#   https://pdm-project.org/en/latest/usage/project/#commit-your-pdmlock-file-to-version-control
# pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/pypa/pipflow and pdm
__pypackages__/

